com.canoo.dolphin.client.javafx.view

Class AbstractViewBinder<M>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.canoo.dolphin.client.javafx.view.AbstractViewBinder<M>
  • Type Parameters:
    M - type of the model
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractFXMLViewBinder

    public abstract class AbstractViewBinder<M>
extends Object
    A abstract JavaFX view controller that can be used as a basic for a JavaFX based view. Each instance will automatically trigger Dolphin Platform to create a controller instance on the server that is bound to the view instance and shares a model (see DolphinBean) with the view.

    • Method Detail

      • init

        protected abstract void init()
        This method will automatically be called after the controller instance has been created on the server and the initial model is snychronized between client and server. When this method is called the model can be accessed (by calling getModel()) and actions can be triggered on the server controller instance (by calling invoke(String, Param...)).

      • destroy

        public CompletableFuture<Void> destroy()
        By calling this method the MVC group will be destroyed. This means that the controller instance on the server will be removed and the model that is managed and synchronized between client and server will be detached. After this method is called the view should not be used anymore. It's important to call this method to removePresentationModel all the unneeded references on the server.
        Returns:
        a future can be used to react on the destroy

      • invoke

        protected CompletableFuture<Void> invoke(String actionName,
                                         com.canoo.dolphin.client.Param... params)
        This invokes a action on the server side controller. For more information how an action can be defined in the controller have a look at the DolphinAction annotation in the server module. This method don't block and can be called from the Platform thread. To check if an server
        Parameters:
        actionName - name of the action
        params - any parameters that should be passed to the action
        Returns:
        a future can be used to check if the action invocation is still running
